# Smart Hiring Backend Analysis Report

This report provides a detailed analysis of the **Smart Hiring** backend codebase. The application is built as a RESTful web service using **Java 21**, **Spring Boot 4.0.6**, **Spring Security**, **Spring Data JPA**, and **PostgreSQL** (hosted via Supabase), securing endpoints using stateless **JSON Web Tokens (JWT)**.

---

## 1. System Architecture & Tech Stack

The application follows a standard layered architecture:
```
[Client (e.g., React App)]
         │
         ▼
[Spring Security Filter Chain (JwtFilter)]
         │
         ▼
[Controllers]  <-- Receives requests, maps DTOs
         │
         ▼
[Services]     <-- Houses business logic
         │
         ▼
[Repositories] <-- JpaRepository for DB interaction
         │
         ▼
[Database (PostgreSQL / Supabase)]
```

### Key Technical Details
- **Java version:** 21
- **Spring Boot version:** 4.0.6
- **Database:** PostgreSQL (Supabase)
- **Security:** Stateless Spring Security, JWT (using JSON Web Token API `0.11.5`), BCrypt hashing for passwords.
- **Boilerplate Reduction:** Lombok

