        String location
        String salary_range
        LocalDate opened_date
        LocalDate closing_date
        Long recruiter_id FK
        LocalDateTime created_at
    }
    job_applications {
        Long id PK
        Long candidate_id FK
        Long job_id FK
        String resume_link
        String status
        LocalDateTime applied_at
    }
    users ||--o{ jobs : "posts (recruiter_id)"
    users ||--o{ job_applications : "applies (candidate_id)"
    jobs ||--o{ job_applications : "receives (job_id)"
```

### Table Mappings
1. **`users`**: Stores user accounts. The `role` column holds either `RECRUITER` or `CANDIDATE`.
2. **`jobs`**: Stores job postings. Linked to `users` via `recruiter_id`.
3. **`job_applications`**: Maps candidates to job postings. Features a unique constraint `uniqueConstraints = @UniqueConstraint(columnNames = {"candidate_id", "job_id"})` ensuring a candidate cannot apply to the same job multiple times.

